      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FERNCO NEL NZ (8) made a winning return to Brisbane when he came from a 10m handicap and scored by 5 metres last start, taking his record at this circuit and distance to six from nine. That was his first start for close to two months so it should have improved him. Talented and draws for a trail. Strong claims. FRENCH FRIES (6) has yet to miss the top-three this time in and was good from a similar draw last start, digging deep to get home by a neck over this distance. Race fit so can go close again. TEN DA TOUCH NZ (3) brings good form from Melton where he has produced two close-up efforts since winning from a wider barrier. A good draw could see him measure up. QUADDIE VC NZ (1) has been tackling standing start races of late but is well served by the ace draw and strikes at 50 per cent at this distance.",
